      "type": "message",
      "text": "I tweeted this recently: <https://twitter.com/stathissideris/status/1099322082905808896> - it’s about my efforts to query the Clojure AST using datalog from the REPL. The same system also supports querying information about the actual invocations of functions and the data that was passed to them, so eventually you’d have a hybrid static/dynamic analysis. It’s still at the proof of concept stage so I think it hasn’t realized its full potential, but I’d be interested about what you think about it.",
